### 6.3 -- Color contrast fixes

The `#868686` on white fails WCAG AA (contrast ratio ~3.5:1). The token `--text-muted: rgb(130, 130, 130)` also fails at 3.5:1. For date/metadata text, keep the muted color (decorative), but for any actionable or meaningful text, use `--text-secondary` (75, 75, 75 = 5.6:1 ratio, passes AA).

Specific fix: `.collection-date-created` color should use `var(--text-secondary)` not `var(--text-muted)`.

